challengeName: PoC OCR to XML In Java - Part 2
detailedRequirements:
Task Overview

We have recently completed a PoC challenge to build a java command line utility to convert a pdf containing images to a machine-readable XML format using OCR technology. We recieved different approaches to address the requirements, one of them is using UZN format to OCR the images.

The goal of this challenge is to improve this solution as outlined below.

Task Requirements

The solution is using ImageMagick to convert PDF to images, tesseract ORC to do the actual OCR of images, simple-xml to convert the OCRed text to machine-readable XML format. The solution contains a README file detailing how to setup and run the utility.

You are addressing the following in this challenge :

  • Remove dependency on ImageMagick and and replace it with Tess4J. Use it also to do the actual OCR instead of the current implementation.
  • Update the logic to run as follow :
    • Convert PDF to Images
    • For each image - determine if the page is supported or not.
    • Group images that of the same type.
    • For each group of images, run the parser to OCR it and return the XML.
    • Construct the XML and validate it against a configured XSD file.
  • Restructure the solution, the current implementation put all code in single class OCRtoXML, use the facade pattern and adapter pattern to implement a flexiable solution (Check High Level Class Diagram below) :
    • OCRtoXML is entry point of the utility
    • OCRtoXML should hold "Analyzer" array field :
      • The field should be loaded via reflection from configuration. The Analyzers should share same interface but have different implementation.
      • After converting pdf to images, the utility will do the following :
        • Iterate over each analyzer in the array and pass the page image as input.
        • Group the images that is supported by the analyzer and run the parser.
        • If none of the pages is supported by parser, simply continue to next analyzer.
    • Parser Interface
      • We will have a separate Parser implementation class for each supported page format.
      • It will holds list of uzn files.
      • Parser will have a function that accepts an array of image pages as input, will OCR the image and return a valid XML.
    • Analyzer Interface
      • This will be similar to Parser implementation class but will only run OCR using uzn configuration to recognize if the page can be parsed or not.
      • It holds list of uzn format files.
      • It should reference an instance of the parser as well, created via reflection with info from configurations.
      • It has a function that accepts one image page as input, it will use the configured uzn file format to parse the fixed content in the page to verify if the page corresponds to it's parser or not.
      • If the page supported, it will return return, otherwise, false.
  • Update code to support parsing multiple pages of the same format.
  • All code should be well documented.
  • Cleanup all code, and remove useless configuration, files, ..etc.
  • Write a detailed deployment document.

Supported Pages Formats

We currently support only two pages formats, you can read about them from the previous challenge. When analyzing the pages we will the following :

  • For Main Report page :
    • Report Title, Application Number, and Table headers are fixed content, will never change. So you need to code the analyzer to parse these areas using uzn files in the input image, and verify the content are the expected strings, then return true if valid. Otherwise, return false.
  • For Annex report page :
    • The report title, and the table headers are fixed content, will never change. So you need to code the analyzer to parse these areas using uzn files in the input image, and verify the content are the expected strings, then return true if valid. Otherwise, return false.

The parsers will do the full OCR uzing all uzn files.

Configuration

Configuration should be in XML format. The uzn files does not have to be configured in the XML.

Documents

Provided in challenge forums the existing solution, XSD file, and few samples of input files and their output.

Test

We will use the samples to test your solution, the output is expected to match the provided output samples. Make sure to test them thoroughly.

Deliverable

  • A Fully implemented solution that addresses the requirements above.
  • A detailed readme to setup and run the tool.
